result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Court is in trial and unable to hear this case.  Parties emailed new court dates.  Case adjourned, Br. 41.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for November 17, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jose Ramon Duenas Jr appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Christopher John Ertl appeared by video for Jose Ramon Duenas Jr.  Prosecuting attorney Josh Milder in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for Status Conference. Attorney Ertl informs court that there has been a breakdown in communication that is irreconcilable.  Motion of the defense counsel to withdraw granted by the Court.  Attorney is to inform the Public Defender's Office that new counsel needs to be appointed.  Case is adjourned for status of counsel to Br 41.
Status conference scheduled for October 6, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for Level 4 Supervision.  
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Jose Ramon Duenas in court with attorney Christopher John Ertl.  Julie D Knyszek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: SD.  
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Attorney Ertl requests additional status conference in order to be appointed by the public defenders office.  Case adjourned, Br. 41.  Status conference scheduled for September 22, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with TMB.
